<subSubSection id="FB390368C90EF1C5A16A6477B64F3653" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C676C11E1EACA389D78AB632F5DDE5CD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B7EE6C5E99FD493FAAE7F8D1F988ACFC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Medium-sized species, 7.3-8.7mm. Body brown. Elytra with fine dense punctures. Discs of pronotum and elytra smooth, lacking reticulate microsculpture.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B9DC329D996DFEE1D074B0B50D2B4A13" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="redescription">
<paragraph id="C4A89192B070985A696DB499266AFBD6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Redescription.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="468E7770FF4197B168DF73EA5C1F6980" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Length 7.3-8.6 mm, width 3.4-4.0 mm. Head and prothorax reddish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="226E5711F6509E3F541BBCE04A460B94" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Habitus of Pyrrhalta igai Kimoto and P. meihuai sp. nov. A P. igai, female, dorsal view B ditto, ventral view C ditto, lateral view D P. meihuai sp. nov., female, dorsal view E ditto, ventral view F ditto, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545548" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">18D-F</figureCitation>
), but antennae black; scutellum and elytra yellowish brown; meso- and metathoracic ventrites, and legs black. Eyes small, interocular space 2.24-2.76 
<normalizedToken id="90868A3A0382C31CCD3E2014DCAA2AC5" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
diameter of eye. Antennae filiform in males (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AFC21EEF140ED4732624C4BFCC669D97" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta meihuai sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F gonocoxae G spermatheca H abdominal ventrite V, female I abdominal ventrite V, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545552" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">22A</figureCitation>
), gradually broadened from antennomere V to X, length ratios of antennomeres I-XI 1.0: 0.6: 0.7: 0.7: 0.8: 0.7: 0.8: 0.8: 0.7: 0.7: 0.9, length to width ratios of antennomeres I-XI 2.8: 2.1: 2.2: 2.2: 2.6: 2.2: 2.4: 2.3: 2.0: 1.9: 2.7; similar in females (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A3F74301744B06C4407849FF048A580D" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta meihuai sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F gonocoxae G spermatheca H abdominal ventrite V, female I abdominal ventrite V, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545552" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">22B</figureCitation>
), length ratios of antennomeres I-XI 1.0: 0.6: 0.8: 0.6: 0.7: 0.7: 0.8: 0.7: 0.8: 0.7: 0.9, length to width ratios of antennomeres I-XI 2.7: 2.2: 2.2: 2.0: 2.1: 2.2: 2.1: 1.9: 2.2: 2.0: 2.8. Pronotum and elytra convex. Pronotum 2.2-2.3 
<normalizedToken id="A9352FCAF05A6A5BF98965B7B9D8E230" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
wider than long, disc smooth; with extremely dense, coarse punctures, and long pubescence, with median longitudinal and lateral depressions; lateral margins slightly rounded, widest at middle, apical margin slightly concave, basal margin straight; anterior and posterior setiferous punctures not erect. Elytra broad, parallel-sided, 1.6 
<normalizedToken id="374956D12EB52AF05BD12209E5759406" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide; disc smooth, with dense, coarse punctures, and short pubescence. Apical spur of tibia of middle leg absent and tarsomere I not modified in males. Aedeagus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D3BB32D51864A1B07DE8256879679137" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta meihuai sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F gonocoxae G spermatheca H abdominal ventrite V, female I abdominal ventrite V, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545552" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">22C, D</figureCitation>
) broad in dorsal view, 5.4 
<normalizedToken id="0D75E0BC3C9CA83B6C4B84A4ACB23F89" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as aedeagus, with several teeth along lateral margin near apex, secondary sclerite small and wide, 0.2 
<normalizedToken id="44B79FC31714604395A3A279030D70E3" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as primary sclerite. Only apices of gonocoxae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="48EEA689A7D34A0CAE4B84383237EA5F" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta meihuai sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F gonocoxae G spermatheca H abdominal ventrite V, female I abdominal ventrite V, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545552" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">22F</figureCitation>
) sclerotized, longitudinal, with dense, long setae along lateral and apical margins. Ventrite VIII (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="40472672090389F4FC4152F11B5C5EBE" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta meihuai sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F gonocoxae G spermatheca H abdominal ventrite V, female I abdominal ventrite V, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545552" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">22E</figureCitation>
) well sclerotized, sides strongly curved, with dense, long setae laterally, apical area, and along apical margin, spiculum extremely long. Receptacle of spermatheca (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3FE612909A63EE16005C1571AAE46045" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta meihuai sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F gonocoxae G spermatheca H abdominal ventrite V, female I abdominal ventrite V, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545552" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">22G</figureCitation>
) very swollen; pump long and strongly curved; sclerotized proximal spermathecal duct wide and short. Apical margin of abdominal ventrite V broadly rounded with deep depression at middle in males (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9E5D38310420FA3C8F4F865BB073ADD3" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta meihuai sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F gonocoxae G spermatheca H abdominal ventrite V, female I abdominal ventrite V, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545552" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">22I</figureCitation>
); while lacking depression in females (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7FE8B54B93078F41A317DD037839B5A0" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta meihuai sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F gonocoxae G spermatheca H abdominal ventrite V, female I abdominal ventrite V, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545552" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">22H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
